iting for you at the safe spot.<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Ulyn Vindix<br>Registered User<br>(4/21/02 4:15:19 pm)<br>Reply  Re: I agree<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br> &lt;g&gt;<br><br>Sorry Aerimus, when I see you posting about Rogues needing liftaps, track, levitate, golem-wand summoning skills and AE deathtouch I sometimes have time differentiating the intentionally humerous suggestions  <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Methinks you got yourself a reputation of a whiner? <p>Aurore<HR>~Seekers of Divinity~<BR>Sorceress of <a href=http://www.ralloszek.net>Rallos Zek</a><BR><a href=http://www.progressquest.com><img src=http://www-rocq.inria.fr/~bnguyen/pony.gif></img></a>The Pony with the Pointy Hat.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujeshuah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jeshuah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/21/02 9:26:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=68.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Exodus vs escape</span><hr size=1> I agree with Aerimus, Escape should take a rogue off someone's target in PvP.<br><br>Isn't evasion a major aspect of the rogue class?  Practically everyone at lvl 60 has see invis up, so sneak/hide isn't that powerful at all in PvP (at least on Sullon Zek, I don't know about Rallos).  I think being able to evade people every once in a while in PvP is just as worthy of the rogue class that instant evacuation is worthy of the wizard class. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/21/02 9:32:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=68.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Whatever</span><hr size=1> 1 person in 1 post doesn't make a rep.  I have a reputation of looking at the pvp system and finding faults and making suggestions.  <br><br>Whether those suggestions are always spot on or if they always take every possible situation into acount is up for discussion but the holes are real and discussion is how you figure shit out.<br><br>The pvp system is without a doubt broken in many respects.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uneyfearsthe2nd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neyfears The2nd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/22/02 7:48:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=68.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Manaburn WILL NOT BE NERFED ;P</span><hr size=1> From dev team at Seattle Fanfair <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>&quot;* Manaburn will _not_ be getting nerfed. The dev team is perfectly happy with it currently. They are aware of what a group of MB wizards can do to Kunark mobs, but they said that a wizard with Ice Spear can nuke Emperor Crush in one shot and progression happens.&quot;<br><br><br><br>Oh well :P  Finally, balance in PvP..<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uauroreakengro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aurore Akengro</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/22/02 10:32:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=68.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I couldn't help it :P</span><hr size=1> I also agree the PvP system is broken. I also agree that everyone has see invis up (probably since level 4 actually). I do think that hide is useless with regards to that (except if target is dispelled and has no perma invis item) and that a way of moving off target would be nice... but when on that thread you put a post on that thread explaining how this is a taunt towards wizards, I have to doubt your real motivations. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaerimusshadowborn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aerimus Shadowborn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/22/02 11:27:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=68.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Mannaburn and exodus</span><hr size=1> Firstly &quot;<br><br>* Manaburn will _not_ be getting nerfed. The dev team is perfectly happy with it currently. They are aware of what a group of MB wizards can do to Kunark mobs, but they said that a wizard with Ice Spear can nuke Emperor Crush in one shot and progression happens.&quot;<br><br>That spoke to the pve aspect of the skill and the general feeling from verant that it wasn't overpowering in pve.  It mentions nothing about pvp and the omission leads me to believe that either<br><br>A) Its a non issue and not worth mentioning.  This is not the case.  Verant went to the trouble of stating that it was &quot;totally broken in pvp&quot; and had &quot;slipped through the cracks&quot;  Even if this was no longer the case they would I think adress the fact that they had changed their minds.<br><br>B) The person that was spoken with had little personal interest or information on the subject and thus wasn't aware of or didn't adress the issue.  Verant employees are hardly all knowing when it comes to their game I would personally rate that tidbit of info as utterly inconclusive and wait for a more final verdict.<br><br>Next Exodus.  I thought to laugh at some people who rated that skill as overpowered then turned around and defended exodus and nexus gate. Cause basicly it would be and has been deemed overpowered on the rogue boards when the idea of hide not being seen by see invis has come up.  <br><br>The posters who did comment more rationally conceded that skill might be ok rather than take the hypocritical position that exodus and nexus gate should be as they are and escape should remain as they are.  Grats to you.  However I still think the idea of an instant escape is overpowering. <br><br> I wouldn't mind terribly if escape was altered as I suggested and nexus gate remained the same. In fact I'm better off supporting this position.  The chance of nexus gate and exodus being changed is slim indeed.  The chance of escape being altered is at least a bit better.  <br><br>Would kind of suck to be one of the 12 classes without an instant escape though.  I think its hilarious that the CT potions now take you to a 50+ raid zone <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign